National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: Kansas City, MO
Accident Number: CEN11CA314
Date & Time: 05/02/2011, 0422 CDT
Registration: N50KP
Aircraft: PRICHARD KEVIN LEGACY 2K
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Loss of visual reference
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis The pilot arrived at his intended destination about 90 minutes prior to the beginning of civil twilight.
He stated that he was cleared to land and subsequently landed off the runway and struck an airport sign, which caused substantial damage to the airplane.
He added that requesting for the runway lights to be turned up, better familiarization with the airport, flying a longer approach, or executing a go-around might have prevented the accident.
He stated that there were no failures or malfunctions related to the airplane prior to the accident.
Federal Aviation Administration inspectors stated that the pilot had been cleared to land on runway 1L and misjudged the approach.
Investigation Docket: http://dms.ntsb.gov/pubdms/search/dockList.cfm?mKey=79009
